detail:
آخر الأسبوع
ʔāḵer il-ʔusbūʕ
the weekend

هاي آخر مرّة بستنّاك.
hāy ʔāḵer marra bastannāk
This is the last time I'm waiting for you.

مش عارف إيمتى آخر مرّة سمعت هالجملة.
miš ʕāref ʔēmta ʔāḵer marra smeʕt hal-jumle
I don't know when the last time I heard that sentence was.

انا آسف، نسيت أحكي معك مبارح.
ʔana ʔāsef, nsīt ʔaḥki maʕak mbāreḥ
I'm sorry, I forgot to talk with you yesterday.

آلة تصوير
ʔālet taṣwīr
camera

لازم أبعد عن التلفون — هيك عمري ما بعمل إشي.
lāzem ʔabʕed ʕan it-tilfōn — hēk ʕomri mā baʕmal ʔiši
I have to get away from the phone — like this I won't ever get anything done.

definition: (by extension) to deport, to banish, to exile, to expel

detail:
الدوا مش مأثّر فيه.
id-dawa miš mʔaṯṯer fīh
The medicine doesn't affect him.

قديش الأجار؟
ʔaddēš il-ʔajār?
How much is the rent?

لغة أجنبيّة
luḡa ʔajnabiyye
foreign language

كان لازم يأجّلو العرس.
kān lāzem yʔajjelu l-ʕoros.
They had to postpone the wedding.
خلّينا نأجّل هالموضوع ليوم تاني.
ḵallīna nʔajjel hal-mauḍūʕ la-yōm tāni.
Let's put off this subject for another day.

الصليب الأحمر
iṣ-ṣalib il-ʔaḥmar
the Red Cross

إمّي أخدت معها الأكل لستّي.
ʔimmi ʔaḵdat maʕha il-ʔakl la-sitti
My mother took the food for my grandmother with her.
لازم ناخد تكسي لأنّه السيّارة مع مرتي
lāzem nāḵod taksi laʔinno is-sayyāra maʕ marti
We have to take a taxi because my wife has the car.
خد شمال من الإشارة وبعدين ضلّ دغري.
ḵod šmāl min il-ʔišāra w-baʕdēn ḍall duḡri
Take a left at the traffic light (lit. signal), then keep (going) straight.
برافو حبيبتي، أخدتي القرار الصحّ.
brāvo ḥabībti, ʔaḵadti il-qarār iṣ-ṣaḥḥ
Bravo my dear, you made (lit. took) the right decision.

أحمد أخد الكتاب من صاحبه.
ʔaḥmad ʔaḵad li-ktāb min ṣāḥbo
Ahmad got the book from his friend.

الخطّ الأخضر
il-ḵaṭṭ il-ʔaḵḍar
the Green Line

الحدّ الأدنى للدفع خمسين شيكل.
il-ḥadd il-ʔadna lad-dafeʔ ḵamsīn šēkel
The minimum payment is fifty shekels.
The minimum limit for payment is fifty shekels.

شو رايك أروح عندك ومرّة تانية منأرجل؟
šu rāyak ʔarūḥ ʕindak w-marra tānye minʔargel
What do you say I come over to your place and we smoke argileh at another time?

بتشرب أرجيلة؟
btišrab ʔargīle
Do you smoke hookah?

لقيت ميّتين شيكل عالأرض.
laʔēt miyytēn šēkel ʕal-ʔarḍ
I found two hundred shekels on the ground.

أرنب بري
ʔarnab barri
hare

على أساس إنّ
ʔala ʔasās inn
on the basis that..., on the condition that...

آخر الأسبوع
ʔāḵer il-ʔusbūʕ
the weekend

الجليل الأسفل
il-jalīl il-ʔasfal
Lower Galilee
الناصرة السفلى
in-nāṣre s-sufla
Upper Nazareth

رقم التلفون بكون مكتوب أسفل الصفحة.
raqam it-tilfōn bikūn maktūb ʔasfal iṣ-ṣafḥa
The phone number is written at the bottom of the page.

definition: to indicate, to point to, to hint to

detail:
إجى الباص وأشّرتله.
ʔija l-bāṣ w ʔaššart-illo.
The bus came and I signaled to it.

definition: elative degree of عالي‎ (ʕāli): higher, highest, maximum
detail:
الحدّ الأعلى للسرعة ستّين كيلومتر بالساعة.
il-ḥadd il-ʔaʕla las-surʕa sittīn kīlomitr bis-sāʕa
The maximum speed limit is sixty kilometers per hour.

الجليل الأعلى
il-jalīl il-ʔaʕla
Upper Galilee
الناصرة العليا
in-nāṣre l-ʕulya
Upper Nazareth

همّه الأغلب بتأخّرو، لإنّه فيه أزمة كتير بالطريق من نابلس.
homme il-ʔaḡlab bitʔaḵḵru, laʔinno fīh ʔazme ktīr biṭ-ṭarīʔ min Nāblis.
They will (the) most likely be late, because there's a lot on traffic on the way from Nablus.

definition: plural of فكرة‎ (fikra, “(a single) idea, thought”)
plural of فكر‎ (fikr, “idea, thought, notion, belief”): way of thinking, ideology
detail:
كلّ اللي أخدو أفكار الشيوعية تخيّب أملهم في النهاية.
kull illi ʔaḵadu ʔafkār ash-shi’uiyye tḵayyab ʔamalhom fin-nihāye
All those who embraced the ideas of socialism were disappointed in the end.

الحدّ الأقصى
il-ḥadd il-ʔaqṣa
the maximum

definition: elative degree of كتير‎ (ktīr): more, most
more, -er; most, -est (used to form elatives of adjectives, that don't have one.)
detail:
مجنون أكتر
majnūn ʔaktar
crazier
أكتر واحد مجنون
ʔaktar wāhad majnūn
the craziest one

definition: elative degree of كتير‎ (ktīr): more, most
detail:
أكتر إشي حبيته
ʔaktar ʔiši ḥabbēto
the thing I liked the most

لقیت الفار ماكل الجبنة.
laʔēt il-fār mākel il-jibne
I found the mouse had eaten the cheese.

أكم من بيضة بدك أعمللك؟
ʔakam min bēḍa biddak ʔaʕmel-lak?
How many eggs do you want me to cook for you?

قلتلّه أكم من مرّة، بس هو ما بوخد كلامي صحّ.
ʔoltillo ʔakam min marra, bas huwwe ma bōḵed kalāmi ṣaḥḥ.
I told him a few times, but he doesn't take me seriously at my word.

لسّا ما أكّدو الأخبار.
lissa ma ʔakkadu l-ʔaḵbār.
They haven't confirmed the news yet.
لازم نأكّد ولادنا إنّه ما يحطّو تمّهم على أي إشي بمكان عامّ.
lāzem nʔakked ūlādna ʔinno mā yḥoṭṭu timmhom ʕala ʔayy ʔiši bi-makān ʕamm.
We must ensure that our children not put their mouth on anything in a public place.

ما رح ألهيك عن شغلك اليوم.
mā raḥ ʔalhīk ʕan šuḡlak il-yōm
I won't distract you from your work today.

اللغة الأم
il-luḡa il-ʔumm
native language, mother tongue

ألف شيكل ممكن اعطيك — أمّا ألفين، هلا والله ما بقدر.
ʔalf šēkel mumken aʕṭīk, ʔamma ʔalfēn halla walla mā baʔdar.
I can give you a thousand shekels — as for two thousand, I really can't right now.
كل هادا، معليش — أمّا يكذب علي كمان؟
kull hāda, maʕlēš — ʔamma yikzeb ʕalay kamān?
All of this is fine — but that he should lie to me too?

definition: used to indicate surprise or other strong feelings in an exclamation
detail:
دخلنا جول — أمّا شو جول!
daḵalna gōl — ʔamma šū gōl!
We scored a goal — what a goal!

definition: to insure, to secure, to safeguard
detail:
سيّارتك مأمّنة؟
sayyārtak mʔammane?
Is your car insured?

definition: (formal) to confer favour, to bestow favour
detail:
الله ينعم عليك!
ʔaḷḷa yinʕim ʕalēk!
May Good give you pleasure! (response to نعيما‎ (naʕīman))

ما كنت بدي اهينك.
ma kunt biddī ʔahīnak
I didn't want to offend you.

definition: or (mutually exclusive, when used together with إما‎ (ʔimma))
detail:
إما بتدفع كاش أو بالكرت.
ʔimma btidfaʕ kāš ʔaw bil-kart
Either you pay cash or by card.

أوضة النوم
ʔōḍt in-nōm
bedroom
أوضة الصفرة
ʔōḍt iṣ-ṣufra
dining room

كيف كان أوّل يوم مدرسة؟
kīf kān ʔawwal yōm madrase
How was the first day of school?

بقى عنده أكزخانة يشتغل فيها.
baʔa ʕindo ʔakzaḵāne yištḡel fīha.

فيه حدا جاي غيري؟
fīh ḥada jāy ḡēri
Is anyone coming aside from me?
هو دايمًا بيجي عالوقت المناسب.
huwwe dāyman bīji ʕal-waʔt li-mnāseb
He always comes at the appropriate time.
إجى الجيش بقوّة عيسكريّة كبيرة.
ʔija l-jēš bi-ʔuwwa ʕaskariyye kbīre
The army came with a lot of (lit. big) military power.
إجت شويّة قهوة على قميصي.
ʔijat šwayyet ʔahwe ʕala ʔamīṣti
A little coffee got on (lit. came to) my shirt.
تعال عندي (لعندي) نحكي شويّ عن الموضوع.
taʕāl ʕindi (la-ʕindi) niḥki šwayy ʕan il-mōḍūʕ
Come over to my place to talk a bit about the issue.

من أوّل ما إجيت وإنتي بتحطّي مكياج.
min ʔawwal mā ʔijīt w ʔinti bitḥoṭṭi mikyāj
You've been putting on makeup from the moment I arrived.
Since as soon as I arrived you're putting makeup.

definition: (+ ل‎) to come up to, to approach
detail:
إجتلي وطلبت منّي أعملّها معروف.
ʔijat-li w-ṭalbat minni ʔaʕmil-lha maʕrūf
She came up to me and asked me to do her a favor.

definition: (by extension) to get, to receive (with recipient as direct object)
detail:
إجاني كتير تلفونات من عيلتي اليوم.
ʔijāni ktīr telefōnāt min ʕēlti l-yōm
I got a lot of calls from my family today.
إجتني فرصة أروح أدرس طبّ في بريطانيا.
ʔijatni furṣa ʔarūḥ ʔadros ṭibb fi brīṭānya
I got an opportunity to go study medicine in the UK.

definition: (by extension) (+ في‎) to fit (in a space)
detail:
ولا يمكن هالخزانة تيجي بالغرفة.
wala yumken hāl-ḵazāne tīji bil-ḡorfe
There's no way this wardrobe will fit in the room.

للأسف البنطلون ما بيجي علي (على قدّي) منيح.
lil-ʔasaf il-banṭalōn ma bīji ʕalay (ʕala ʔaddi) mnīḥ
Unfortunately the pants don't fit me well.

definition: to come right on time, with perfect timing, etc.
detail:
مبارح جوزي فاجأني بسفرة عاليونان — عن جد إجا عالوجع․
mbāreḥ jōzi fājaʔni bi-safra ʕal-yūnān — ʕan jadd ʔija ʕal-wajaʕ
Yesterday my husband surprised me with a trip to Greece — it really came right on time.

عشان أوفّر مصاري، جبت صاحبي يصلّحلي التلّاجة — بس إجا يكحّلها عماها․
ʕašān ʔawaffer maṣāri jibt ṣāhbi yṣalleḥ-li it-tallāje bas ʔija ykaḥḥelha ʕamāha
To save money, I brought my friend to fix the fridge for me — but he only made matters worse.

إسأله إذا المدير موجود.
ʔisʔalo ʔiza l-mudīr mawjūd
Ask him if the manager is there.
ما بعرف إذا برجع ولّا لأ.
ma baʕref ʔiza birjaʕ willa laʔ
I don't know whether he's coming back or not.
إذا رجع بكير، بقلّك.
ʔiza rijeʕ bakkīr, baʔul-lak
If he gets back early, I'll tell you.

أخدت إذن من أهلك عشان تروح على هالرحلة؟
ʔaḵadt ʔizn ʕašān trūḥ ʕala hār-riḥle
Did you get permission from your parents to go on the trip?

الإسلام بصومو في شهر رمضان.
il-ʔislām biṣūmu fi šahr ramaḍān.
Muslims fast in the month of Ramadan.

إشي ضلّو، إشي راحو
ʔiši ḍallu, ʔiši rāḥu
Some stayed, some left

definition: to; for (detached version of the indirect object suffix ـلـ‎ (-l-), used for emphasis)
detail:
كتب إلي، مش إلك.
katab ʔili, miš ʔilak.
He wrote to me, not to you.

هالكتاب إلك.
hāl-kitāb ʔilak
This book is yours.
هو صاحب إله.
huwwe ṣāḥeb ʔilo
He's a friend of his.

إلي أخ وأخت.
ʔili ʔaḵḵ w-ʔuẖt
I have a brother and sister.
Mine are a brother and a sister.

الساعة خمسة إلا تلت.
is-sāʕa ḵamse ʔilla tult
It's twenty to three.

إما بتدفع أجار البيت أو بترحل.
ʔimma btidfaʕ ʔajār il-bēt ʔaw btirḥal
Either you pay the rent or you get out.

definition: if (followed by a past tense verb)
detail:
إن جيت بكرة، جيبلي معك جاكيت.
ʔin jīt bukra jīb-li maʕak jākēt
If you come tomorrow, bring me a jacket.
If you come tomorrow, bring for me a jacket with you.

بدي أعرف إنكنه فاضي بكرة.
biddi ʔaʕref ʔinkann-o fāḍi bukra
I wan't to know if he's free tomorrow.

هو دايما بنسى يغسّل إيديه.
huwwe dāyman binsa yḡassel ʔīdēh
He always forgets to wash his hands.

أخيرًا أخدنا الإجازة اللي كننا كتير محتاجينها الصيف الماضي
ʔaḵīran ʔaḵadna il-ʔijāze lli kunna ktīr miḥtājīin-ha iṣ-ṣēf il-māḍi
We finally took the vacation we were really needing last summer.

خلّينا نعمل نسخة تانية للاحتياط.
ḵallīna niʕmil nusḵa tānye lil-iḥtiyāṭ
Let's make a second copy just in case (lit. for the precaution).
ماما أخدت احتياطها وعملت أكل زيادة بحالة إنّه إجو ناس أكتر.
māmā ʔaḵdat iḥtiyāṭha w-ʕimlat ʔakl zyāde bi-ḥāle ʔinno ʔiju nās aktar
Mom took precautions and made extra food in case more people come.

هي احمرّت من الخجل.
hiyye iḥmarrat min il-ḵajal
She blushed out of embarrassment.

تطلّع على كلّ أنواع هالبوظة — مش عارف شو بدّي أختار.
itṭallaʕ ʕala kull ʔanwāʕ hāl-būẓa — miš ʕāref šu biddi ʔaḵtār
Look at all these ice cream flavors — I don't know what to choose.
إذا اخترتو تروحو على هالرحلة هادا إشي برجعلكم.
ʔiza iḵtartu trūḥu ʕala hāl-raḥle hāda ʔiši birjaʕ-ilkom
If you choose to go on the trip, that's up to you.

اخترعو رمز سرّي يبعتولكم ايّاه أولادكم لمّا يحسّو حالهم بمواقف مش مريحة.
iḵtirʕu ramz sirri yibʕatū-lkom iyyāh ūlādkom lamma yḥessu ḥālhom bi-mawāʔef miš murīḥa
Invent a secret message for your kids to send you when they feel themselves in uncomfortable situations.

تلفوني كان هون واختفى.
telfōni kān hōn w-iḵtafa.
My phone was here and now it's gone.
My phone was here and it disappeared.

definition: to be at ease or comfortable with something
detail:
انا بالمرّة ما ارتحت.
ana bil-marra mā rtaḥt
I wasn't comfortable at all.
خبّرني إذا فيه أي إشي ما ارتحتيله.
ḵabbirni ʔiza fīh ʔayy ʔiši mā rtaḥtīlo
Let me know if there's anything you're not comfortable with.

بدّي استأجر غرفة.
biddi staʔjer ḡorfe.
I want to rent a room.

definition: to be shy, to be ashamed, to be embarrassed
detail:
استحيت أسأله.
istaḥēt asʔalo.
I was embarrassed to ask him.

هو مش عارف يستخدم الكمبيوتر.
hū miš ʕāref yistaḵdem il-kambyūter.
He doesn't know how to use the computer.

لمّا بدرس للامتحانات، بالعادة باخد استراحة واحدة بس لمدة نصّ ساعة.
lamma badros lil-imtiḥānāt bil-ʕāda bāḵod istirāḥa wāḥde bas la-moddet nuṣṣ sāʕa
When I study for exams, I usually just take one half-hour break.

definition: to slacken, to loosen, to become limp

detail:
بدي أضلّ بالبيت وأسترخي.
biddi ʔaḍall bil-bēt w ʔastarḵi.
I want to stay home and relax.

definition: to consult, to seek someone's advice
detail:
بعد ما استشرت المحامي، قرّرت إنّي ما أستثمر بالمشروع لأنّه القانون ما بضمنلي حقّي.
baʕd mā istašart il-muḥāmi qarrart ʔinni mā ʔastaṯmer bil-mašrūʕ laʔinno il-qānūn mā biḍman-li haʔʔi
After I consulted the attorney, I decided not to invest in the project, because the law doesn't guarantee my rights.

استعرت منّه أكمّن كتاب
istaʕart minno ʕakammin kitāb
I borrowed several books from him.

استعملنا كلّ الطرق.
istaʕmalna kull iṭ-ṭoroʔ.
We employed every method.

definition: to find (something) weird, strange, odd, unusual, funny
detail:
بستغرب منّك كيف بتيجي هون مرّة تانية.
bastaḡreb minnak kīf btījī hōn marra tānye
I can't understand how you could come here again.
I find it strange from you how you come here a second time.

بيستغلّو العمّال
bistaḡellu il-ʕummāl
They exploit the workers.

definition: to do, manage, get along without
detail:
بتقدر تستغني عنه؟
btiʔdar tistaḡni ʕano
Can you manage without him?

definition: to benefit or profit from, to make use of
detail:
بصراحة بستفيد كتير من محاضراته.
bi-ṣarāḥa bastafīd ktīr min muḥāḍarāto
Honestly, I get a lot out of his lectures.

استقبلني في مكتبه.
istaʔbalni fī maktabo
He received me in his office.

خلّينا نستنّى نشوف شو بتحكي المسّ
ḵallīna nistanna nšūf šū btiḥki il-miss
Let's wait to see what the teacher says.

منستورد بضاعتنا من الخارج.
mnistawradd bḍāʔatna min il-ḵārej
We import our goods from abroad.

اسم العيلة
ʔism il-ʕēle
surname, family name
اسم الشخص
ʔism iš-šaḵṣ
first name
شو اسمك؟
šu ʔismak?
What's your name?
شو الاسم الكريم؟
šu l-ʔism il-karīm?
What's your noble name?

شسمك ؟
šismik
What's your name?

ما ختارش اسم باهي لكتابه
mā ḵtāriš ʔism bāhi liktābu
He didn't choose a good title for his book

كنت في البحر واسمرّيت كتير.
kunt fi-l-baḥr w-ismarrēt ktīr
I was at the sea [beach] and I got really tanned.

ما تنسو تشتركو بالقناة.
mā tinsu tištirku bil-qanā.
Don't forget to subscribe to the channel.

definition: to participate, to take part, to join in

detail:
ممكن تشتري ضوّ من الضواو المدوّرة العاديّة تبعة الموجة الجديد.
mumkin tištri ḍaww min iḍ-ḍwāw li-mdawwra l-ʕādiyye tabʕat il-mūje li-jdīde
You can buy a light from the normal circle lights of the new trend.

ما اشتغلت مبارح.
mā ištaḡalt mbāreḥ
I didn't work yesterday.
شو بتشتغل؟
šū btištḡel?
What do you do for a living?
what do you work?
لازم نبدا نشتغل عالمشروع الإنجليزي.
lāzem nibda ništḡel ʕal-mašrūʕ il-ʔinglīzi
We have to start working on the English project.

أنا شخصيّا بعتبرها من أكتر حركات الدبكة سهولة.
ʔana šaḵṣiyyan baʕtber-ha min ʔaktar ḥarakāt id-dabke shūle
I personally consider it one of the easiest dabke moves.

بفتخر إني مسلم
baftaḵer inni muslim
I'm proud to be Muslim (lit. I am proud that I am Muslim)

ḵabbarat ṣāḥebātha yḡasselu ʔīdēhom mnīḥ ʕašān nimnaʕ intišār il-ʕadwa
She told her friends to wash their hands well in order to prevent the spread of the infection.

كاسة مي
kāset mayy
a glass of water

استنى علي شوي تألبس المداس.
istanna ʕalayy šwayy ta-ʔalbis il-madās.

كلّ قديش بتروح عالنادي؟
kull ʔaddēš bitrūḥ ʕan-nādi?
How often do you go to the gym?

هي ناصحة شوي.
hiyye nāṣḥa šway
She's a bit plump.

بنام شوي بعد الغدا.
banām šway baʕd il-ḡada.
I sleep a little bit after lunch.

نام عالكنبة وارتاح.
nām ʕal-kanabe w-irtāḥ.
Lie down on the couch and relax.

أنا ناوي أروح عالبحر اليوم.
ʔana nāwi ʔarūḥ ʕal-baḥr il-yōm
I'm intending to go to the sea today.

هو ناوي يساعدني، بس على شرط إنّي أساعده كمان.
huwwe nāwi ysāʕidni bas ʕala šarṭ ʔinni ʔasāʕido kamān
He's willing to help me, but on the condition that I help him too.

definition: a little bit, a small amount
a little bit, a small amount
detail:
الأكل بدّه نتفة ملح.
il-ʔakl biddo nitfet mileḥ
The food needs a pinch of salt.

طرد نحل
ṭard naḥl
a swarm of bees

definition: to go down, to come down
detail:
شفتها نازلة من عنده.
šuftha nāzle min ʕendo.
I saw her coming down from his place.
كل شهر بنزل على يافا.
kull šahr banzal ʕala yāfa.
Every month I go down to Jaffa.

definition: (by extension) to get off, to disembark
detail:
نزلت من الباص.
nzilt min il-bāṣ.
I got off the bus.

definition: (by extension) to flow, to drip, to leak
detail:
دمّه نازل.
dammo nāzel.
He's bleeding.
His blood is flowing.
الميّ نازلة من الحنفية.
il-mayy nāzle min il-ḥanafiyye.
The water is leaking from the faucet.

فيه مكان تنزل فيه في رام الله؟
fī makān tinzal fī fi ramallah?.
Is there a place for you to stay in Ramallah?

ما تنسي تحطّي اسمي عالمشروع، آه؟
mā tinsi tḥoṭṭi ismi ʕal-mašrūʕ, ʔāh
Don't forget to write my name on the project, yeah?
كنت ناسي بشكل عام انّك بتنبسط لهالدرجة هون.
kunt nāsi bi-šikl ʕām innak btinbisiṭ la-hād-daraje hōn
I had forgotten in general that you enjoy yourself so much (lit. to this degree) here.

نصّ الليل
noṣṣ il-lēl
midnight

جوز نضّارات
jōz naḍḍārāt
a pair of glasses
نضّارات شمسيّة
naḍḍārāt šamsiyye
sunglasses

أقنعت نفسي.
ʔaqnaʕt nafsi
I convinced myself.
المشية ممكن تسمعوها بأكتر من اسم، بس إحنا تركيزنا عالحركة نفسها.
il-mašye mumken tismaʕūha bi-ʔaktar min ism, bas ʔeḥna tarkīzna ʕal-ḥarake nafsha
You can hear "il-Mashye" go by more than one name, but our focus is on the move itself.

هادا نفس الشي.
hāda nafs iš-šī
That's the same thing.

definition: to be beneficial, to be useful
to be suitable, to be fitting

detail:
عندك فكرة وين في رام الله بنفع أنام، أنا وتنين صحابي؟
ʕindak fikra wēn fi rām allah binfaʕ ʔanām, ʔana w-tnēn ṣḥābi
Do you have any idea where in Ramallah I can sleep, me and my two friends?
بتوقّع بنفع نلتقي السبت بكل الأحوال.
batwaʔʔaʕ binfaʕ niltʔi is-sabt bi-kul il-ʔaḥwāl
I expect we can meet on Saturday in any case.

definition: (transitive) to move, to pass on, to transfer
detail:
لازم نلبس الكمّامة عشان ما ننقل العدوى اللي حوالينا.
lāzem nilbis il-kammāme ʕašān ma nonʔol il-ʕadwa illi ḥawālēna
We should wear the mask so as not to pass on the infection that is around us.

نهر الأردن
nahr il-ʔurdon
River Jordan

صباح النور
ṣabāḥ in-nūr
good morning
morning of the light

definition: a unisex given name, Noor, from Arabic

detail:
غرفة النوم
ḡurfet in-nōm
bedroom

definition: The thirty-ninth letter of the Pashto alphabet.
The ninth letter of the Yorùbá alphabet in the Ajami Script.
A letter of the Ottoman Turkish alphabet.
The thirty-first letter of the Perso-Arabic alphabet. It is preceded by و‎ and followed by ی‎. Its name is هه‎/هِ‎ (in Iran) or هی‎ (Classical Persian and Dari).

detail:
هالكتاب
hal-kitāb
this book
هالسيّارة
has-sayyāra
this car
هالولاد
hal-ūlād
these kids

بطاقة الهويّة
biṭāqat il-hawiyye
identity card

definition: he; masculine third-person singular proximal personal pronoun
this way (i.e., direction), that way (i.e., direction) (e.g., to look this or that way, i.e., in this or that direction)

(by extension) this, that; used as a pronominal object of قال‎ (ʔāl, “to say”), فكّر‎ (fakkar, “to think”), and similar transitive verbs of expression, عِمِل‎ (ʕimil, “to do”) and synonyms, and comparative مِن‎ (min, “than”).
detail:
ليه قلت هيك؟ ليه عملت هيك؟ فكرتك أفضل من هيك
lē ʾilt hēk? lē ʿmilt hēk? fakkartak ʾafḍal min hēk
Why did you say that? Why did you do that? I thought you were better than this.
Why did you say so? Why did you do so? I thought you better than so

definition: such; such kind, this kind of
detail:
ما فيي اتحمل هيك حكي منك!
Ma fīyi tḥammal haik ḥaki minnak.
I can’t stand this kind of talk on your part.

definition: so, thus, like this, like that
detail:
مش هيك؟
miš hēk?
Isn't that so?
لازم تعمله هيك.
lāzem tiʕmelo hēk
You have to do it like this.

هو أطول من هيك.
hū ʔaṭwal min hēk
He's taller than that.
ما قلتش هيك.
ma ʔult-š hēk
I didn't say that.
I didn't say so.

ما بحبّ أتعامل مع هيك ناس.
mā baḥebb ʔatʕāmal maʕ hēk nās
I don't like to interact with such people.
كان فيه تلاتة أربعة هيك شي.
kān fīh talāte ʔarbʕa hēk ši
There were about three or four.
There were three, four, something like that.

قال هيك هيك.
qāl hēk hēk
He said such-and-such.

أعطيني مكتوبك، هيك هيك أنا رايح عالبوسطة.
ʔaʕṭīni maktūbak, hēk hēk ʔana rāyeḥ ʕal-bōsṭa
Give me your letter, I'm going to the post anyway.

هيّ الكتاب اللي سألتني عنّه.
hayy li-ktāb illi saʔalt-ni ʕanno
This here is the book you asked me about.

definition: (by extension) used to stress the current nature of an action
detail:
هيّني جاي من البنك.
hayy-ni jāy min il-bank
I'm coming right now from the bank.
هيّ فيه واحد طالع من ورا الشجرة.
hayy fīh wāḥad ṭāleʕ min wara š-šajara
There's someone coming out right now from behind the tree.

definition: A letter of the Ottoman Turkish alphabet.
The thirty-eighth letter of the Pashto alphabet.
(colloquial, Iranian Persian, Iran) Shortened form of رو‎ (ro); both are spoken forms of را‎ (râ).

detail:
مبيّن إنّك مبسوط وإنتا بتعلّم.
mbayyen ʔinnak mabsūṭ w-inta bitʕallem
It's clear that you're happy when you're teaching.

حَاجْتِي بْقْلَمْ وكَرّاسَة
ḥājtī b-qlam u karrāsa
I need a pencil and a copy-book.

definition: The thirty-third letter of the Urdu abjad.
The thirty-ninth of the Ushojo abjad.
The twenty-fourth letter of the Yoruba alphabet in the ajami script, equivalent to Latin script w.
The thirtieth letter of the Perso-Arabic alphabet. It is preceded by ن‎ and followed by ه‎. Its name is واو‎.

detail:
وادي رمّ
wādi ramm
Wadi Rum (in Jordan)

بدّيش اشوف وجهك مرّة تانية.
biddīš ašūf wijhak marra tānye.
I don't want to see you (lit: your face) again.

definition: sheet of paper, piece of paper
detail:
ورقة شدّة
waraʔet šadde
a playing card

الغرفة ما بتوسع كل الناس
il-ḡorfe mā btūsaʕ kull in-nās
the room won't fit everyone

definition: (transitive) to extend, to expand, to make space
detail:
بدّنا نوسّع الصالون
baddna nwasseʕ aṣ-ṣālōn
We want to extend the living room.

definition: (transitive) to take, to convey, to deliver
detail:
بابا، بصير توصّلني عند صاحبتي اليوم؟
bābā, biṣīr twaṣṣelni ʕind ṣāḥebti l-yōm
Dad, could you take me to my friend's place today?

definition: to recommend (that someone to do something)
detail:
بوصّيك انّك تتوجّه للدكتور.
bawaṣṣīk ʔinnak titwajjah lad-doktōr.
I recommend that you go to the doctor.
I ask you that you direct yourself to the doctor.

وّصاهم علي للوضيفة.
waṣṣāhom ʕalay lil-waẓīfe.
He recommended me to them for the position.
He asked them for me for the position.

definition: to request, to order, to ask (someone to do something) (+ على‎)
detail:
وصّيت على طاولة؟
waṣṣēt ʕala ṭāwle?
Did you order a table?
آه، وصّيته على طاولة.
ʔā, waṣṣēto ʕala ṭāwle
Yes, I asked him for a table.

وقع من شجرة و انكسرت ايده.
wiʔiʕ min šajara w-inkasarat ʔīdo
He fell from a tree and broke his hand (lit. his hand broke).

وقع منّك الجزدان
wiʔiʕ minnak il-juzdān
You dropped your wallet (lit. the wallet fell from you).

وقّفت كتير استنّاك بالشارع.
waʔʔaft ktīr astannāk biš-šāreʕ.
I stood for a long time waiting for you in the street.
حكومة ايرلندا بتوقّف ضدّ نظام الاحتلال الإسرائيلي.
ḥukūmet irlanda bitwaʔʔef ḍidd niẓām il-ʔiḥtilāl il-ʔisraʔīli.
The Irish government stands in opposition to the Israeli occupation regime.
هيّني وقّفت عالدور.
hayyni waʔʔaft ʕad-dōr.
I just got in line.
I just stood at the turn.

definition: to stand up, to get up
detail:
اللي بدّه ييجي معي لازم يوقّف هلا.
illi biddo yīji maʕi lāzem ywaʔʔef halla.
Whoever wants to come with me should get up now.

كان مفروض توقّف معي.
kān mafrūḍ twaʔʔef maʕi.
You were supposed to stand up for me.

إذا كانو يتنمّروك، ليش ما وقّفتلهم؟
iza kānu yitnammarūk, lēš mā waʔʔaft-ilhom?
If they were bullying you, why didn't you stand up to them?

ساعتي وقّفت.
sāʕti waʔʔafat.
My watch has stopped.
كان يحكي عادي، بس لمّا فاتت عالغرفة وقّف بسرعة.
kān yiḥki ʕādi, bas lamma fātat ʕal-ḡurfe waʔʔaf bsurʕa.
He was speaking normally, but when she came into the room he quickly stopped.

definition: (transitive) to stop, to put an end to
detail:
الشرطي وقّفني عشان ما كنت حاطط حزام الأمان.
iš-šurṭi waʔʔafni ʕašān mā kunt ḥāṭeṭ ḥizām il-ʔamān.
The policeman stopped me because I hadn't put my seatbelt on.
المدير وقّف التدخين بالمكتب.
il-mudīr waʔʔaf it-tadḵīn bil-maktab.
The manager put an end to smoking in the office.

الشركة رح توقّف ميّة عامل عن الشغل في مصنعها الرئيسي.
iš-širke raḥ twaʔʔef miyyet ʕāmel ʕan iš-šuḡl fi maṣnaʕha ir-raʔīsi.
The company will lay off one hundred workers at its main factory.

definition: (by extension) to arrest, to detain, to hold
detail:
وقّفوه لتحقيق.
waʔʔafūh la-taḥʔīʔ.
They held him for interrogation.

وقّف السيّارة قدّام العمارة.
waʔʔaf is-sayyāra ʔuddām il-ʕamāra.
He parked the car in front of the building.

definition: (transitive) to stand up to, to go against, to confront
detail:
الشرطة بتهاجم مين ما وقّف بوجه النظام الراسمالي.
iš-šurṭa bithājem mīn mā waʔʔaf bi-wijh in-niẓām ir-rasmāli.
The police attacks anyone who goes against the capitalist system.

definition: (transitive) to be on one's side, to support
detail:
إنتا كصاحبي لازم توقّف في صفّي ضدّه.
enta ka-ṣāḥbi lāzem twaʔʔef fi ṣaffi ḍiddo.
As my friend you need to stand on my side against him.

ما بدي هادا ولا هادا.
mā biddi hāda wala hāda.
I neither want this nor that.

هاد ولد جديد بصفّي.
hād walad jdīd bi-ṣaffi
This is a new kid in my class.

بدك هادا ولا هادا؟
biddak hāda willa hāda?
Do you want this or that?

definition: where (relative and interrogative adverb, also figuratively)
detail:
من وين إنت؟
min wēn ʾinta? (to a male), min wēn ʾinti? (to a female)
Where are you from?
عم تقلي روح إحكي معها؟ هي وين وأنا وين؟
ʿam tʾilli rūḥ ʾiḥki maʿa? hiyyi wēn wʾana wēn?
You’re telling me I should go talk to her? She’s way out of my league.
You’re telling me to go talk to her? Where is she and where am I?

من وين بتيجي كلمة (أوضة)؟
min wēn btīji kilmet ʕōḍa?
Where does the word ʕōḍa come from?
وينك؟ ليش ما عمّ بتبيّن؟
wēnak? lēš mā ʕamm bitbayyen
Where are you? Why haven't you been showing up?

definition:
union, connection, joining
c. 1260s,  Jalāl ad-Dīn Mohammad Rūmī, Reynold A. Nicholson, transl., مثنوی معنوی‎ [Masnavi-ye-Ma'navi], volume I, verse 937:
detail:
قابل امر ویی قایل شوی / وصل جویی بعد از آن واصل شوی‌‌
qâbel-e amr-e vey-i qâyel šavi / vasl juyi ba'd az ân vâsel šavi
If you accept His command, you will become the spokesman [thereof]; if you seek union [with Him], thereafter you will become united.

definition: c. 1260s,  Jalāl ad-Dīn Mohammad Rūmī, Reynold A. Nicholson, transl., مثنوی معنوی‎ [Masnavi-ye-Ma'navi], volume I, verse 937:
detail:
قابل امر ویی قایل شوی / وصل جویی بعد از آن واصل شوی‌‌
qâbel-e amr-e vey-i qâyel šavi / vasl juyi ba'd az ân vâsel šavi
If you accept His command, you will become the spokesman [thereof]; if you seek union [with Him], thereafter you will become united.

definition: accusative particle, used with pronominal suffixes to express English object pronouns, like me, him, etc.
detail:
شو بدك ياني قول؟
šū baddak yāni ʔūl?
What do you want me to say?
رح فرجيك ياهن.
raḥ farjīk yāhun.
I'll show them to you.
ما فيني اشرحلك ياه.
mā fīni ʔišraḥ-lak yā.
I can't explain it to you.

معيش وقت اليوم — يا بروح عالنادي يا بشوف صحابي.
maʕīš waʔt il-yōm — ya barūḥ ʕan-nādi ya bašūf ṣḥābi
I don't have time today — I either  go to the gym  or  see my friends.

يا ريتك هون.
ya rētak hōn
I wish you were here.
يا ريت إنجليزيتي زيّ العربي تبعك.
ya rēt ʔinglīziyyti zayy il-ʕarabi tabʕak
I wish my English (were) like your Arabic.

يلا نروح على بركة.
yaḷḷa nrūḥ ʕala birke
Let's go to a pool.

يلا باي
yaḷḷa ḅāy
bye-bye

لف عإيدك اليمين!
liff ʕa-ʔīdak il-yamīn!
Turn right!
Turn on your right hand!

definition: Alternative spelling of ايا‎ (iyya-), especially after a vowel
